# TW Live Design System & Style Guide

## Overview
This is a Vue 2 + Vuetify sports timing and live event management platform with a comprehensive design system built on CSS custom properties.

## Core Design Files
- Colors: [frontend/src/assets/styles/colors.css](mdc:frontend/src/assets/styles/colors.css)
- Typography: [frontend/src/assets/styles/defaults.css](mdc:frontend/src/assets/styles/defaults.css)
- Breakpoints: [frontend/src/assets/styles/sizes.css](mdc:frontend/src/assets/styles/sizes.css)
- Custom Font: [frontend/src/assets/fonts/Petrov Sans-Trial/petrov-sans-trial.css](mdc:frontend/src/assets/fonts/Petrov Sans-Trial/petrov-sans-trial.css)

## Brand Identity
- **Primary Brand Color**: `--accent: #1a9ad7` (Blue)
- **Secondary Brand**: `--ffr-brand: #009eda` (FFR Blue)
- **Success Color**: `--success: #46C289` (Green)
- **Error Color**: `--message-error: #D94D58` (Red)

## Typography System
- **Primary Font**: "Petrov Sans-Trial" (Custom font with multiple weights)
- **Font Stack**: "Petrov Sans-Trial", Avenir, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif
- **Letter Spacing**: 0.01em standard
- **Responsive Font Sizes**: Defined in media queries for different screen sizes

## Color System
### Light Theme
- Background Primary: `--background--primary: #dadadf`
- Background Card: `--background--card: rgba(242,242,248,0.92)`
- Text Default: `--text-default: #080811`
- Text Muted: `--text-muted: #757589`

### Dark Theme
- Uses `.theme-dark` class
- Background Primary: `--background--primary: #2f2f34`
- Background Card: `--background--card: rgba(16,16,24,0.92)`
- Text Default: `--text-default: #f2f2f7`

## Responsive Breakpoints
- Desktop 2K: 2560px
- Desktop Big: 1980px
- Desktop Small: 1280px
- Tablet Default: 920px
- Tablet Small: 720px
- Mobile Default: 640px
- Mobile Small: 480px

## Spacing & Layout
- Uses 8pt grid system
- Mobile-first responsive design
- CSS Grid and Flexbox for layouts
- Custom scrollbar styling

## Usage Guidelines
1. Always use CSS custom properties (CSS variables) for theming
2. Follow mobile-first responsive approach
3. Use semantic color names (primary, success, error) over descriptive ones
4. Maintain WCAG AA accessibility standards
5. Use the custom Petrov Sans font family as primary typeface
6. Implement proper dark/light theme support with `.theme-dark` class
